caption: dropped in on mon i think. next time i'll be back with my coworkers. they have a lot of great reviews for a reason.
Fun place to hang out with locals on Bourbon Street
I know that when you’re drunk everything tastes good but not this alligator sausage pop boy! Don’t waste your time! Find a batter place!

Probably the worst place, they didn’t have bread and every sandwich needs bread..and the person taking care of you was too busy talking to her significant other instead of taking care of you.. many other good places to go to for good food and service. But not here.

Came in. Horrible service. Tried to order a sandwich from the menu was told it cannot be ordered because its not an option on the register?? Ordered a different sandwich, after ordering was told there is no buns for the sandwich??  Had to wait for manager to get my money back....
Place blows. Garbage jambalaya
Lousy service, mediocre food...

I’m a local....   the roast beef po boy is good but very skimpy.    The boudin is not too bad but it’s ok.   The Jambalaya is terrible.   Just a bowl of rice with one little sausage.   Overall not worthy of its Bourbon St location.
Good bar. Good folks
Best real deal po boy awesome gumbo too! Every time we come to New Orleans where I was he here never disappointed!

Roast beef PoBoy! The Best in New Orleans in my opinion. They do it right! Conveniently located on Bourbon Street. Small hole in wall kind of place but I believe it is actually part the world famous Court Of Two Sister's Restaurant as it is located right behind it. Another one of our favorite places to get a PoBoy in the French Quarter.

It’s a cute little hole in the wall. I got the seafood gumbo and it was good for my first time having it. My friend got the beans and rice and said it was good as well. It was a nice place and not as crowded as others places here

Freakin awesome! My sister and I got the shrimp Po-Boy, seafood gumbo combo and it was the perfect taste of New Orleans. The staff was so nice and helped us pick the best for our experience! Thank you!
The food is not good. My jambalaya is just a rice bowl. No sausage, no chicken, no onion, peppers, nothing but rice, not even spicy

This place sucks. "Jambalaya" was just brown rice in a bowl. Po-boy bread was stale and hard, with a hole carved out in order to fit food.  Get in Uber to Melba's instead, for the best po-boy in the city. Do NOT eat at Court Tavern.
Sad excuse for a muffaletta. Avoid.

Wish I could give zero stars. Employees were disinclined to serve us food. Can't imagine the quality of the food given the awful service. I've seen enough Kitchen Nightmares that I can only guess how many multi legged critters were nesting in the gumbo.
Employees are lethargic.  Food is terrible. They'll charge you for extra food you didn't order.
The food is equally as bad as the customer service.
Both employees had their backs to the counter when I walked up. They were too busy on their phones to notice I was there for a few minutes. The food was good and not too expensive.

This place is great. Every year when I go back to NOLA, (and I'm born and raised nola) I make it a point to eat here.  The people aren't rude, there is no "racial divide" that exists. It's a local, authentic place to grab a bite to eat that's extremely delicious. Lose the attitude and high standards prior to walking in the door and you just might enjoy yourself!

First place I ate after arriving in New Orleans and this place left a bad taste in my mouth about food all over the French Quarter. Well actually it left no taste in my mouth. Red beans and rice and the gumbo were completely bland. Like, I mean no flavor. It’s pretty bad when the best part of a meal is a hot dog.
Food was pretty good, too bad the cashier was extremely rude, and yelled at us because we were trying to decide what to get to drink.  Good food, bad cashier, no wonder why they’re always empty....

I have no idea what people are complaining about. I am a professionally trained chef. The food here is good. Is it a 5 star establishment? No. It's a hole in the wall serving delicious down home food. The red beans and rice while a touch bland, was spot on. The boudin was pretty good. I spent $250 at a famous New Orleans establishment on Royal St also named "court", that has two trees in the courtyard and would gladly have been back at court tavern.

I wish I could leave zero starts. We were here on vacation and honestly really enjoyed the southern hospitality. That all ended on our last day in NOLA when we visited this establishment. First we were not really acknowledged when we entered. But when we were we were told to "order where the sign says order here" despite that we decided to order. The sign outside said they had amazing Boudin, so that's what I ordered. But had questions about the rest of my order. The guy who took my order very sarcastically said "dang, how many questions you gonna ask". Since this place was recommended we ordered and figured the food would be better than the service. Were we wrong. We watched them MICROWAVE our food. it's an open "kitchen " so you can see everything. My wife and I looked at each other hoping that they were not microwaving our food. Unfortunately they were. The Boudin was advertised as spicy.... Not everything was just a rubbery mess. We didn't ... Couldn't even eat the food. Do not eat here unless you like microwaved false advertisement and rude service. We should have known from the empty seats this could not be good.
Chips were stale and disgusting and the sausage was bland with no flavor. Only plus was it was not raw.

I had the roast beef poboy and the top bread was brick hard and the bottom soggy from all the gravy that was poured on it. It was served with a variety pack of regular lays chip that one would buy for a kids school lunch. The Jambalaya was like Zatarain's with a link sausage thrown on top. Both these "dishes" were $10 each and not worth it.
This place was terrible. Worst Poboy I’ve ever had.  Shrimp was literally frozen.  Unless you are drunk to the point that your tastebuds are not working avoid this place at All costs.

Hubby's alligator sausage poboy was ok, but the roast beef poboy "mystery gravy", a salty sause with the roast beef soaked in it. What is really wrong here is their snotty cashier. Are you kidding me? If she is so unhappy she should find another job. Flies and birds are everywhere too. Yuck! $30 for 2 poboys and 2 drinks.

Tonight's experience Longest wait time EVER. The STAFF especially the cashier with the long braids is rude as ever, I asked a question she ignored me and rolled her eyes, they stopped taking orders without alerting the long line to clean. Crazy part is I went to Nola last year and experienced the same thing. I used to like the andolli sausage but not anymore. Food is bland, smells good though, but not. Do yourself a favor eat somewhere else with much better food and service until they get a much better manager, menu and staff!
A few friends and I ate here and the food is horrible.  Done waste your time or money. 🤮
Food was mediocre but commanded premium prices; on top of that there is no bathroom inside, and the forks and knives are made of very weak plastic.
For the price.. the "half" of the gator poboy was decent.. but the  jambalaya was horrible.. very dry like it was sitting for a veerry long time

(Translated by Google) No toilet :(  Beer is bigger than my head! :)  Very very average food. It helps out what! : /  (Original) Pas de toilette :(  La bière est plus grosse que ma tête! :)  Nourriture très très moyenne. Ça dépanne quoi! :/

Staff was friendly and helpful with picking items on the menu. The cold boiled shrimp po boy was amazing and the jambalaya was good too. It's relatively cheap and easy to get in and out of while walking bourbon street. Not sure why this place doesn't get better reviews except that people are spoiled and expect Michelin service at McDonald's prices
Mediocre food and pitiful service. Should have kept on walking.
Just bought a moufeletta with NO meat inside! $10 got cheese, olives, and bread. Maybe they just forgot about it 🤷🏽‍♀️ nice people thou
Worst service ever. Food is already made and they just microwave it to order. With an attitude.

If I could give it a zero I would. This Iowa farm boy makes better red beans and rice than this NOLA establishment. I was very disappointed. The food tasted like it came off a truck precooked with no seasoning of any kind.  A basic Subway sandwich would have been better tasting.
I don't care for anything on the menu except the boudin. We trekked over here a second time after finding how good it was. I was extremely disappointed with them only having cold shrimp poboys! WTH.
Mushy bouidin, small (not jumbo) shrimp on the po' boy, dry and tasteless jambalaya...all over-priced garbage. Avoid!
Bread was stale. Food was not fresh. Disappointed
Food is solid, and our girl Laquisha was a ton of fun and super helpful!
I really loved the muffaletta and the counter staff were very friendly, helpful, and our food was ready super fast! Seemed like mostly locals eating there.

It is simple and authentic. Nothing fancy. We stopped to check out the menu and saw locals eating there so thought we would try it. The gumbo was legit! Really hit the spot. Tried a bit of my brother-in-law's muffaletta and it was great. The olive mix was amazing. The bread was warm and soft and oh so yummy. Atmosphere is low-key with counter service. A nice break from the crowded loud atmosphere of Bourbon Street. You can get your grub on then get back at it without having to pay for heavy cover charges or hype.
very very bad food from a very very gross place staffed by very very incompetent people. avoid at all costs.  literally anywhere else is better.
MICROWAVE! Everything is microwaved and not authentic.

Food is nothing to write about. The irony. The staff is just as bad. My gf and I came and ordered a muffuletta and jambalaya, which were both disappointing. Firstly, the muffuletta had barely any meat, a grand total of 3 thinly sliced meats. The BREAD of the sandwhich was pretty much your main course which was chewy and tough. The Jamabalaya was a small serving which was dry and rice was close on the crunchy side. Secondly, the STAFF! when we ordered we left tip as a courtesy although we were not waited on. Although we left tip the staff service was horrible. The cashier mentioned that our food was taking a while and it would be out in a bit. I mentioned that was fine but when I looked over a few minutes later the cook and cashier were video chatting and enjoying social hour. I watched for a few minutes and made eye contact with one of the ladies and she proceeded to video chat but at least she took the time to grab and manage a  baquette with her other free hand. I would not recommend this place at all! Service sucks, food sucks and is way over priced. Save your money, time, vacation and taste buds. Now that I think of it the place was empty for a reason, a first thought maybe it was because it was early. #disappointing
I thought the price was okay but the food was substandard, I had a poboy and they gave me a packet of lays crisps from 2015
Ordered boudin, saw them throw it into a microwave throw it on a bun and serve it to me.  Consistency was like bread sausage.  Terrible.

"FOOD POISONING" This has been one of my favorite places to get a roast beef po-boy for years. It's my stop-in place before or after a parade or performance at French Quarter Fest. Yesterday, I had the RB with swiss cheese at 11:30am and by 6pm I vomited at least 6 to 8 times. Couldn't get any work done toady and had to take off work tonight. I had a coffee at Johnny White's in the corner bar on Bourbon and Orleans and then the RB po-boy w/swiss and a rootbeer at The Court Tavern (Sister restaurant  of the Court of Two Sister's) ... this is terrible! I really feel for any tourists who experienced this.

My boyfriend wanted some authentic food and I'm a picky eater. We were really short on time before a tour, and found this place down the street. Really quick service. He got jambalaya, which he said was good. I got a chili dog, which was also good. Super cheap, too! Our whole meal was less than $15.

I didnt see the order here sign and was told very condescendingly that i need to read the signs. I'm sure they get plenty of people here daily but i would not recommend stopping. I made an honest mistake and was treated like i was a dumb-ass. Not impressed and i won't be returning. If you're in New Orleans don't bother with this place. The service is atrocious.
It was OK,. Fast service but just OK food
DONT GO. TOTAL TOURIST TRAP
Gumbo was amazing
This place is over priced and the food is awful.

Yes service was atrocities, or they just hate white people. But I didn't go there to make friends or Unite the racial divide. I went to eat some down home Nawlins food. And that's what I got. the sausage, red beans and rice were the best hands down not just in new Orleans  ANYWHERE, and the gumbo was pretty dam good to.

I have never been to a restaurant that was mad that 15 people just walked in hungry. And please don't think that being a paying customers means you have the right to sit with your party. Their idea is that other people before you may want to sit, my idea is 15 people are about to sit regardless so what difference does it make? Service is ridiculously slow considering they are on Bourbon as well.
The beef poboy was basically inedible.  The beef was so tough I scraped it off and just ate the bread.  I think this place only caters to people so drunk they'll eat anything.  Or try to...
Keep walking! Worst street food in New Orleans hands down
Man wth?!  Ordered the boudin sausage and the texture was mush, as in like mashed potatoes.  It did have a little spiciness but dang.
